other_tests.findings: Fluid-filled and dilated appendix up to 1.3 cm containing numerous intraluminal appendicoliths and surrounding inflammatory change; trace fluid noted along the right pericolic gutter. No evidence of perforation or associated abscess formation. A 1.1 cm left hepatic hypodensity likely representing a cyst or hepatic hemangioma; several smaller hepatic hypodensities likely cysts.
